  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Services.</strong> The Contractor shall provide and procure the delivery of the Goods/Services
    to the satisfaction of CIFOR pursuant to the terms of this Contract.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Specification.</strong> The Goods delivered shall comply with the required specifications
    determined by CIFOR.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Quality.</strong> The Goods shall be of merchantable quality and fit for any purpose which
    is made known by CIFOR or for which the Goods are commonly supplied.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Free from Defects.</strong> The Goods shall be free from defects in material and
    workmanship.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Sample or Description of Goods.</strong> Where the Goods are supplied by reference to a
    sample or description, the Goods shall correspond with the sample or description.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Time is of the Essense.</strong> Time is of the essence for the delivery of goods and/or
    completion of the work described in the PO or in the project schedule. Any delay in
    the delivery of goods and/or completion of the work described therein shall
    constitute a material breach of this contract and the Contractor shall compensate the
    loss of time with the rate set out at xxx% for each postponement day
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    If the Contractor is delayed in the performance of its services due to causes beyond
    the contractor's control, then the time allotted in the project schedule for the
    Contractor's Services shall be extended for the period of such delay or CIFOR shall
    authorize the Contractor to work overtime to make up for such lost time, and the
    Contractor's compensation shall be equitably adjusted.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Variations.</strong> Variations may be initiated by CIFOR at any time prior to completion of the
    services by the Contractor. The Contractor shall submit the new project schedule and
    estimated cost of effecting the variation, based on the rates set out in the PO, to CIFOR
    and obtain the written confirmation and approval of CIFOR before starting work on the
    variation request.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Giving Decisions.</strong> CIFOR shall give its approval for all sketches, designs,
    drawings, reports, documents, recommendations, requests, submissions and other
    matters referred by the Contractor to CIFOR or its authorized representative for
    decision within xxx days from the date of request, so as not to delay or disrupt the
    performance by the Contractor of the Services under this contract
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Breaches and Remedies.</strong> Any of the following will be considered as a breach or
    non-fulfillment of this contract on the part of the Contractor:
  </p>
  <ul class="dashed toc">
    <li class="toc">
      Non-disclosure of any relevant information, whether leading to the approval
      of the project by CIFOR, or whether pertaining to any aspect of the execution
      of the project
    </li>
    <li class="toc">
      Continual lack of progress on the project or lack of fulfillment of the
      Milestones in the agreed upon time
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p align="justify">
    In case of any breach of the obligations and warranties hereunder, CIFOR will have
    the following remedies:
  </p>
  <ol class="bracket toc">
    <li class="toc">to request corrective action for all remedial breaches; or</li>
    <li class="toc">
      to terminate the Contract in accordance with the termination provisions of
      this Contract
    </li>
  </ol>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Cancelation.</strong> This PO is deemed to be cancelled under the following
    circumstances:
  </p>
  <ul class="dashed toc">
    <li class="toc">
      The Contractor is unable to provide the parts or supplies or materials within 1
      (one) week after the issuance of this PO or the agreed upon time and no parts
      or supplies or material alternatives acceptable to CIFOR.
    </li>
    <li class="toc">
      Postponement of project work due to negligence of the contractor which
      brings money consequence to CIFOR
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p align="justify">
    The Contractor's total and cumulative liability for damages payable to CIFOR from
    any cause whatsoever and regardless of the form of action whether in contract or in
    tort or under statutory/strict liabilities or otherwise shall not exceed the amount as
    stated in the PO
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Insurance.</strong> The Contractor acknowledges and understands that CIFOR does not
    maintain and will not obtain insurance of any type to protect the Contractor against
    any loss, damage or injury that may in any way result from the Contractor's
    performance of the services/delivery of goods. The Contractor hereby releases
    CIFOR, and their employees from any and all liabilities for any loss, damage, injury
    or costs relating to the performance of the services/delivery of goods, CIFOR's use
    of the deliverables, or CIFOR's reliance of the services/goods provided hereunder.
  </p>
