<td valign="top" width="47.5%">
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Termination.</strong>
  </p>
  <ol type="1" class="toc">
    <li class="toc">
      CIFOR may terminate this Contract with or without cause upon thirty (30)
      days prior written notice to the Contractor. Upon such termination, CIFOR
      shall pay the Contractor, at the rate set out in the PO for the Services
      satisfactorily performed/the Goods satisfactorily delivered up through the
      date of termination. Notwithstanding any provision in this Contract to the
      contrary, CIFOR will not be required to pay or reimburse the Contractor for
      any Services performed/Goods delivered or for expenses incurred by the
      Contractor after the date of the termination notice that could have been
      avoided or mitigated by the Contractor.
    </li>
    <li class="toc">
      Upon expiry of this Contract or upon termination by CIFOR in accordance
      with its terms, no compensation payment of any form will be payable to the
      Contractor including by reason of termination and the Contractor shall be
      solely responsible for any costs related to employees of the Contractor
      involved in performance of this Contract both during the term of this
      Contract and upon and following its termination.
    </li>
  </ol>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Governing Law and Settlement of Disputes.</strong> This Contract shall be governed by
    and construed in accordance with the laws of the Republic of Indonesia. In case of a
    dispute, the Parties shall convene and try to resolve such dispute in good faith. If the
    dispute cannot be resolved within [60] days after it came up, the dispute shall finally
    and conclusively settled by arbitration in accordance with the United Nations
    Commission on International Trade Law (UNCITRAL) Arbitration Rules
    (UNCITRAL Rules) as at present in force, except to the extent that there are any
    conflicts between the UNCITRAL Rules and the provisions of this Contract, the
    provisions of this Contract shall govern. The seat of the arbitral tribunal will be
    Jakarta, Indonesia. The language of the proceedings will be English.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Force Majeure.</strong> Neither CIFOR nor the Contractor shall be liable for any delay in
    the performance of this Contract, nor for any other breach, nor for any loss or
    damage arising from uncontrollable forces such as fire, theft, storm, war, or any
    other force majeure event that could not have been reasonably avoided by exercise
    of due diligence.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Assignment.</strong> The Contractor's interest in this Contract (including the Contractor's
    duties and obligations under this Contract, and the payables due to the Contractor under
    this Contract) may not be subcontracted, assigned, delegated, or otherwise transferred to
    a third party, in whole or in part.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Entire Agreement; Modifications.</strong> This Contract supersedes all prior agreements,
    written or oral, between the Contractor and CIFOR and will constitute the entire
    agreement and understanding between the Parties with respect to the subject matter of
    this Contract. This Contract and each of its provisions will be binding upon the Parties
    and may not be waived, modified, amended or altered except it is made in writing and
    signed by both CIFOR and the Contractor.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Corrupt Practices.</strong> Each Party hereby undertakes that, at the date of the entering
    into force of the Purchase, its directors, officers or employees have not offered,
    promised, given, authorized, solicited or accepted any undue pecuniary or other
    advantage of any kind (or implied that they will or might do any such thing at any
    time in the future) in any way connected with the Purchase and that it has taken
    reasonable measures to prevent subcontractors, agents or any other third parties,
    subject to its control or determining influence, from doing so.
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    Corrupt Practice(s) shall include Bribery, Extortion or Solicitation, Trading in
    Influence and laundering the proceeds of these practices
  </p>
  <p align="justify">
    <strong>Safety &amp; Heath Procedure.</strong> The Contractor shall take every precaution against
    injuries to persons or damage to property. The Contractor shall establish and
    maintain safety procedures in connection with its work performed to satisfy its
    obligations under this Contract.
  </p>
